Airlines was hit
by an equipment failure that
canceled 2000

01:49.509 --> 01:51.411 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
flights.

01:51.445 --> 01:56.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Southwestern
Pakistan, a suicide
bombing killed at least 67
people today, and

01:56.450 --> 01:58.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wounded scores more.

01:58.218 --> 02:01.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It happened in a hospital in the
city of Quetta.

02:01.521 --> 02:04.858 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jonathan Rugman of Independent
Television
News reports.

02:04.891 --> 02:08.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JONATHAN RUGMAN: Ambulances
usually arrive
at hospitals in a hurry.

02:08.729 --> 02:14.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Quetta this morning, they
were leaving,
ferrying the injured away from
an attack on

02:14.234 --> 02:15.936 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a hospital itself.

02:15.969 --> 02:20.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As smoke filled the corridors,
it quickly
became clear the timing was
deliberate.

02:20.841 --> 02:28.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First, men on a motorbike had
shot dead Bilal
Kasi, a senior lawyer on his way
to court.

02:28.215 --> 02:33.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then the group waited for his
fellow lawyers
to gather here before blowing
them up, the

02:33.720 --> 02:38.992 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so-called double tap, as cynical
as it was
cruel.

02:39.026 --> 02:43.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MERAJ TAREEN, Attorney: After
our bar association
president was targeted, we all
came to the

02:43.663 --> 02:45.499 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
hospital.

02:45.532 --> 02:48.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We were leaving the hospital
after Kasich's
autopsy and the media were
interviewing lawyers

02:48.969 --> 02:50.570 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
when the blast took place.

02:50.604 --> 02:54.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For many minutes, there was
darkness all around
us, and then we heard gunshots.

02:54.941 --> 02:59.346 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JONATHAN RUGMAN: Lawyers
complained to visiting
army chiefs that, while they
haven't been

02:59.379 --> 03:05.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
allowed to drive their cars into
the hospital,
a suicide bomber had managed to
get through,

03:05.419 --> 03:11.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
while the hospital's director
told the press
that just one guard armed with a
baton was

03:11.124 --> 03:17.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in charge of security, which
might seem all
the more scandalous, given that
these pictures

03:17.230 --> 03:22.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from January show the same
hospital, this
time receiving survivors from
another deadly

03:23.003 --> 03:26.973 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
suicide bombing on another
medical facility
in the town.

03:27.007 --> 03:33.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, once again, Pakistanis are
crying out
for security, putting pressure
on their Prime

03:33.613 --> 03:38.318 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Minister, Nawaz Sharif, and his
army chief,
who visited the hospital this
evening.

03:38.351 --> 03:42.989 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"For God sake, don't back off,"
this survivor
told the prime minister.

03:43.023 --> 03:47.094 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"It's a handful of people we
must fight with
all our might.

03:47.127 --> 03:49.029 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Don't lose courage."

03:49.062 --> 03:53.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Both the Islamic
State group and
a breakaway Taliban faction
claimed responsibility

03:53.934 --> 03:55.469 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for the attack.

03:55.502 --> 04:00.173 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Japan's Emperor
Akihito signaled
today he'd like to step down.

04:00.207 --> 04:05.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
