address pre-recorded
and broadcast nationally.

04:12.719 --> 04:19.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMPEROR AKIHITO, Japan (through
translator):
I am already more than 80 years
old, and fortunately

04:19.292 --> 04:21.061 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I am now in good health.

04:21.094 --> 04:25.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, when I consider that my
fitness level
is gradually declining, I am
worried that

04:25.565 --> 04:30.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it may become difficult for me
to carry out
my duties with my whole being as
the symbol

04:30.237 --> 04:32.639 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the state, as I have done
until now.

04:32.672 --> 04:37.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Over the years,
Akihito has
had heart surgery and been
treated for prostate

04:37.777 --> 04:39.446 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cancer.

04:39.479 --> 04:44.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is the 125th emperor in a
dynastic line
that goes back more than 2,700
years.

04:44.951 --> 04:50.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Parts of Eastern
Mexico are reeling
after the remnants of Hurricane
Earl touched

04:50.557 --> 04:54.628 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
