all-around category, which
permits only two
per country.

18:49.695 --> 18:53.899 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Favorite Simone Biles soared to
the number
one spot.

18:53.933 --> 18:59.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Teammate Aly Raisman will join
her in the
finals, edging out 2012 gold
medalist Gabby

18:59.638 --> 19:02.475 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Douglas for the second U.S.
slot.

19:02.508 --> 19:09.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, today, fencer Ibtihaj
Muhammad became
the first American Olympian to
compete wearing

19:09.181 --> 19:11.917 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a Muslim hijab, or head scarf.

19:11.951 --> 19:15.354 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She won her first round, before
being defeated.

19:15.388 --> 19:20.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, uproars over doping
are still swirling
over Rio.

19:20.326 --> 19:26.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russian swimmer Yulia Efimova
faced boos before
a preliminary race on Sunday.

19:26.565 --> 19:30.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She had been banned after
failing drug tests,
and then reinstated.

19:30.102 --> 19:32.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
American Lily King made clear
her displeasure
about Efimova's presence in the
pool.

19:33.005 --> 19:37.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on Saturday, Australian
swimmer Mack Horton
accused his Chinese rival Sun
Yang of being

19:38.010 --> 19:42.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a -- quote -- "drug cheat" and
then beat him
in the 400-meter freestyle.

19:42.782 --> 19:46.819 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Chinese officials have demanded
an apology.

19:46.852 --> 19:51.390 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now for an on-the-ground
perspective from
Rio, I spoke a short time ago to
Christine

19:51.424 --> 19:56.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brennan, a sportswriter and
columnist who's
covering the Games for USA
Today.

19:56.195 --> 19:59.899 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She's also a contributor for ABC
News.

19:59.932 --> 20:01.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Christine Brennan, hello.

20:01.534 --> 20:04.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's been quite a weekend for
the United States
in swimming.

20:05.004 --> 20:06.972 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tell us what it's been like at
the swimming
venue.

20:07.006 --> 20:10.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN, USA Today: I
will tell
you, Judy, it was really an
electric evening

20:10.643 --> 20:15.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and certainly for the United
States last night,
with both Katie Ledecky in the
400 freestyle,

20:15.948 --> 20:20.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
world record performance,
breaking her on
world record by almost two
seconds.

20:20.653 --> 20:25.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then within, what, maybe 20,
30 minutes,
you had that relay, of course,
Michael Phelps

20:25.357 --> 20:30.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
coming back to the pool for the
first time,
31 years old now, his fifth
Olympic Games.

20:30.429 --> 20:32.164 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And what does he do?

20:32.198 --> 20:37.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's in the second leg of that
four-person
relay and he stakes the U.S. out
to a lead,

20:37.069 --> 20:42.341 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and the U.S. -- his two
teammates just came
in and won, beating the French.

20:42.374 --> 20:46.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The crowd, you would have
thought it was a
U.S. crowd, in the sense that
here we are

20:46.712 --> 20:48.514 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in Rio.

20:48.547 --> 20:53.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it was a really majestic
moment, I think,
but with the knowledge that the
fans had that

20:53.419 --> 20:56.755 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they were watching something
special, watching
Michael Phelps return, the
greatest Olympian

20:56.789 --> 20:59.258 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of all time, winning his 19th
gold medal.

20:59.291 --> 21:03.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, those two things back to
back -- and Katie
Ledecky even said it after she
won.

21:03.629 --> 21:05.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She goes, "I think there's going
to be another
gold medal."

21:05.431 --> 21:06.999 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She was the first for the U.S.
in the pool.

21:07.032 --> 21:09.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Usually, the U.S. dominates in
the swimming
pool.

21:09.335 --> 21:11.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think we will see that
over the next
few days as well.

21:11.971 --> 21:14.974 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What is it about
Katie Ledecky?

21:15.007 --> 21:17.042 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What puts her far ahead of the
competition?

21:17.076 --> 21:20.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Well, I think
all of her
opponents would love to know
that.

21:20.312 --> 21:22.748 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She's competing really only
against herself.

21:22.781 --> 21:24.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The 800 freestyle is hers.

21:24.383 --> 21:27.286 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She will be even farther ahead
in that.

21:27.319 --> 21:29.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People should get used to seeing
that.

21:29.221 --> 21:34.894 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's just one of these people
who has a wonderful
attitude about life, super
smart, going to

21:34.927 --> 21:40.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Stanford, and gets it, has a
great perspective,
wonderful family that loves
sports, and also,

21:40.733 --> 21:45.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for herself, just a sense that
she just wants
to better herself.

21:45.237 --> 21:49.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It sounds like a cliche, but she
just goes
out there, follows her coach's
orders, kind

21:49.108 --> 21:53.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the model student, the model
athlete, and
just puts it together, and is
absolutely on

21:53.312 --> 21:56.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
top of her game at the most
important moment
of her life.

21:56.715 --> 22:01.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And Michael
Phelps, as you
said, he's now 31 years old.

22:01.086 --> 22:04.490 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He came into these Games with 18
gold medals.

22:04.523 --> 22:06.959 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He just picked up another one
last night.

22:06.992 --> 22:08.627 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What is he looking to do in Rio?

22:08.661 --> 22:10.863 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Well, he's
got a lot more.

22:10.896 --> 22:12.064 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's just beginning.

22:12.097 --> 22:14.099 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And people are going to say,
what, more Michael
Phelps?

22:14.133 --> 22:15.901 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

22:15.935 --> 22:19.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's got the 100 butterfly, 200
butterfly,
200 individual medley and
probably one more

22:19.505 --> 22:20.472 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
relay.

22:20.506 --> 22:22.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So we're just beginning to see
Phelps.

22:22.641 --> 22:24.076 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And this is shocking.

22:24.109 --> 22:26.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you think about this in
sports, swimming
is a young person's came.

22:26.845 --> 22:28.581 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
As I said, Katie Ledecky is 19
years old.

22:28.614 --> 22:31.650 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Somebody of these people are --
a lot of teenagers
in the pool.

22:31.684 --> 22:32.885 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And here's Michael Phelps, 31.

22:32.918 --> 22:36.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, he has certainly had some
difficulties
in his life.

22:36.255 --> 22:38.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He went to rehab after a second
DUI.

22:38.557 --> 22:41.160 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He has acknowledged his
problems.

22:41.193 --> 22:45.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the fact that he could be so
strong at
31 -- in most sports, he would
long since

22:45.965 --> 22:50.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be retired, in terms of his age
-- and yet
he's just still as dominant as
ever.

22:50.502 --> 22:55.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And then you have
the doping
allegations around the Russians
and others.

22:55.374 --> 22:59.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's already causing a backlash
among a number
of the athletes.

22:59.979 --> 23:01.580 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How is that affecting things
there?

23:01.614 --> 23:04.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: I will tell
you, it's been
really interesting.

23:04.550 --> 23:10.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think the metaphor for the
entire conversation,
Judy, about Russian doping, the
diabolical

23:10.256 --> 23:14.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russian doping machine and the
fact that they
were allowed to compete in the
Olympics, as

23:14.827 --> 23:19.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
opposed to being kicked out, as
I thought
they should be, the metaphor
really is -- the

23:19.298 --> 23:21.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pool is a metaphor for that.

23:21.100 --> 23:26.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The booing for these athletes,
Yulia Efimova
especially, the breast stroker,
loud boos

23:26.805 --> 23:32.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for her, loud boos for the
Russian men's 4x100
freestyle relay team, you never
hear that,

23:32.444 --> 23:33.412 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ever.

23:33.445 --> 23:34.413 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And what is that?

23:34.446 --> 23:35.648 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's the swimmers.

23:35.681 --> 23:37.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's coming especially coming
from the swimming
section.

23:37.516 --> 23:39.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The swimmers know.

23:39.084 --> 23:40.052 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They know.

23:40.085 --> 23:41.553 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're disgusted by this.

23:41.587 --> 23:45.024 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I know people will say, hey,
Lance Armstrong
cheated and Marion Jones.

23:45.057 --> 23:49.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. has probably given the
world the
two worst cheaters ever in Lance
Armstrong

23:49.128 --> 23:50.963 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and Marion Jones.

23:50.996 --> 23:55.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The big difference is that for
Russia it was
government-sponsored,
state-sponsored doping.

23:55.267 --> 24:00.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The equivalent would be if a
member of President
Obama's Cabinet ran a five-year
doping plan

24:00.673 --> 24:06.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the United States involving
the FBI, the
CIA, U.S. Olympic Committee, and
U.S. Anti-Doping

24:06.578 --> 24:07.546 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Agency.

24:07.579 --> 24:09.415 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's how diabolical the
Russian plan was.

24:09.448 --> 24:14.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: One other sport
Gymnastics,
this was the first Olympics
appearance for

24:14.787 --> 24:20.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Simone Biles of the United
States, who she
absolutely lived up to her
billing in that

24:20.292 --> 24:21.593 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
qualifying event yesterday.

24:21.627 --> 24:24.530 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Oh, she sure
did.

24:24.563 --> 24:31.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Think Mary Lou Retton and Gabby
Douglas and
Olga Korbut and Nadia Comaneci
into one.

24:31.837 --> 24:35.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In many ways, we are seeing the
culmination
of an entire sport in one
person.

24:36.008 --> 24:38.110 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Simone Biles is that good.

24:38.143 --> 24:39.812 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And the U.S. team is that good.

24:39.845 --> 24:44.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is a sport the you can have
a point,
a tenth of a point deciding
first, second,

24:44.683 --> 24:46.085 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
third.

24:46.118 --> 24:50.022 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. was 10 points ahead as
a team in
the qualifying yesterday.

24:50.055 --> 24:54.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the team, the U.S. team,
will certainly
win the gold medal, barring some
incredible

24:54.760 --> 24:57.629 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
unforeseen occurrence tomorrow.

24:57.663 --> 24:58.630 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
So there's that.

24:58.664 --> 25:00.199 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's the team competition.

25:00.232 --> 25:03.168 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Then Simone Biles in the
individual all-around,
she is expected to win the gold.

25:03.202 --> 25:07.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then she is expected to go
on to the individual
apparatuses and actually keep
winning gold.

25:07.906 --> 25:12.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Simone Biles, I believe by
the time these
Olympic Games are over, will be
seen as the

25:12.344 --> 25:14.179 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
greatest U.S. gymnast ever.

25:14.213 --> 25:16.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'll tell you, that's saying
something,
because there is certainly a lot
of competition

25:16.882 --> 25:18.751 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for that title.

25:18.784 --> 25:23.088 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally,
Christine, after all
the hype and the negative
stories about Brazil,

25:23.122 --> 25:28.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about Rio running up to these
Olympics, how
do these first few days feel to
you?

25:28.260 --> 25:32.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Judy, I have
to say that
these Games have been a pleasant
surprise.

25:32.631 --> 25:36.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There are issues with
transportation and buses
not coming and things like that,
but it really

25:36.802 --> 25:38.303 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
feels like an Olympics to me.

25:38.337 --> 25:40.973 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when I say that, I mean
everything about
it.

25:41.006 --> 25:45.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The opening ceremony, I thought,
was actually
terrific on a budget.

25:45.043 --> 25:50.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They did more with less, far
less budget than,
say -- far fewer dollars to
spend than Beijing

25:50.482 --> 25:54.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in '08 with their grandiose
ceremony or London
in 2012.

25:54.420 --> 25:57.156 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I thought they did a great
job with a
message, with a conscience.

25:57.189 --> 25:58.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that has carried
over the last
few days.

25:58.957 --> 26:00.893 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have seen good will in many
places.

26:00.926 --> 26:03.929 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of course, I mentioned the
booing, but good
will in many places.

26:03.962 --> 26:05.464 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You have seen great upsets.

26:05.497 --> 26:08.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have seen athletes care so
much about
this.

26:08.033 --> 26:09.735 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And the Games are moving on.

26:09.768 --> 26:10.769 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Knock on wood.

26:10.803 --> 26:12.604 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will see how it goes over the
next two
weeks.

26:12.638 --> 26:14.840 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But they really seem to be going
on just fine.

26:14.873 --> 26:18.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you consider the National
Football League
had to cancel its Hall of Fame
game because

26:18.710 --> 26:23.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of a problem on the field, they
couldn't put
on one football game, and here
Rio is seemingly

26:23.649 --> 26:26.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
them moving ahead with all of
these venues,
and so far, so good.

26:26.985 --> 26:31.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that's in many ways a
big sports upset,
but it's also a nice thing to
see as the Games

26:31.490 --> 26:32.624 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
have started.

26:32.658 --> 26:34.660 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Christine
Brennan, thank you
very much.

26:34.693 --> 26:36.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we look forward to talking
to you in the
days to come.

26:36.929 --> 26:38.263 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: You bet,
Judy.

26:38.297 --> 26:42.501 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

26:42.534 --> 26:51.276 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Stay with us.

26:51.310 --> 26:56.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
efforts to make
peace between high schoolers and
police; and

26:56.548 --> 27:00.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the harmonies of Neko Case, K.D.
Lang and
Laura Veirs.

27:00.586 --> 27:08.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: President Obama has
pledged to
accept 10,000 Syrian refugees by
October,

27:08.093 --> 27:10.729 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
despite resistance playing out
in many communities.

27:10.762 --> 27:16.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Refugees, many of them rootless
for years,
often arrive with significant
medical problems

27:16.101 --> 27:18.270 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and psychological trauma.

27:18.303 --> 27:23.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Sarah
Varney brings
us this report about how one
city, Buffalo,

27:23.342 --> 27:25.310 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
New York, is adapting.

27:25.344 --> 27:30.082 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her story was produced in
collaboration with
our partner Kaiser Health News.

27:30.115 --> 27:36.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Since Murhaf,
Ghenwa, and their
children moved here from Syria,
even mundane

27:36.922 --> 27:40.392 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tasks like cooking and homework
have become
more complicated.

27:40.425 --> 27:44.062 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: They have 10 airplanes.

27:44.096 --> 27:50.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Unaccustomed tote
this new life,
the family relies on help from
Hassan Alishaqi

27:50.569 --> 27:58.577 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from a local resettlement agency
called Journey's
End.

27:58.610 --> 28:03.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Refugee agencies help families
like this one
find housing and jobs, get
medical care and

28:03.849 --> 28:07.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
health insurance and enroll in
English classes
and schools.

28:07.786 --> 28:15.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They fled Syria after civil war
erupted there
in 2011, unleashing an exodus of
more than

28:15.894 --> 28:18.130 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
four million refugees.

28:18.163 --> 28:23.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The destruction and violence
came close to
Murhaf's family during one their
last nights

28:23.068 --> 28:24.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the city of Homs.

28:24.703 --> 28:29.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): Some
bullets came
to my house through the window.

28:29.708 --> 28:33.979 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I was afraid for the safety
of my kids.

28:34.012 --> 28:38.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They never sleep because of --
it's just very
hard for them to sleep.

28:38.884 --> 28:44.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: After a year in
Cairo and exhaustive
security checks, the family
arrived in Buffalo,

28:44.089 --> 28:46.725 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a quiet city on the edge of Lake
Erie.

28:46.758 --> 28:51.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And like many new arrivals here,
they're struggling
with the aftermath of their
horrific journey

28:51.063 --> 28:54.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
as they attempt to build
healthier lives in
their new home.

28:54.666 --> 28:59.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
More than 90 percent of the
refugees who resettle
to New York live in Upstate New
York.

28:59.171 --> 29:02.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The city of Buffalo has become a
welcoming
haven for many of them.

29:02.674 --> 29:07.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But over the last 15 years, the
countries
and conflicts they come from
have changed.

29:07.245 --> 29:10.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the health care needs of
refugees are
changing, too.

29:10.349 --> 29:14.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jericho Road is a community
health center
in Buffalo that has long treated
refugees

29:14.353 --> 29:20.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from some of the world's poorest
countries,
including Myanmar, Bhutan, Sudan
and Somalia.

29:20.659 --> 29:24.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The clinic is a crossroads of
languages and
customs.

29:24.262 --> 29:28.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
New refugees receive free
medical assistance
from the federal government for
eight months.

29:28.600 --> 29:31.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then they can buy private
insurance or enroll
in Medicaid.

29:31.236 --> 29:32.938 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

29:32.971 --> 29:35.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MYRON GLICK, Jericho Road: When
you came,
we found that your T.B. test was
positive.

29:35.807 --> 29:39.845 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I think you are now taking
medicine for
that, right?

29:39.878 --> 29:47.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The clinic's
founder, Dr. Myron
Glick, often treats refugees for
tuberculosis,

29:47.653 --> 29:51.690 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
malaria and childhood
malnutrition.

29:51.723 --> 29:56.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he says the more recent
arrivals from
Iraq and Syria, which are
middle-income countries,

29:56.862 --> 30:05.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
typically don't suffer from
diseases of poverty,
but instead have been
traumatized by war.

30:05.570 --> 30:10.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A critical report by local
leaders that examined
the area's safety net found that
health care

30:10.208 --> 30:15.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
providers urgently need to
improve culturally
appropriate mental health
services.

30:15.647 --> 30:20.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And more clinics needed to
follow Jericho
Road's model, hiring refugees
who can help

30:20.085 --> 30:21.987 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
new arrivals adjust.

30:22.020 --> 30:29.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kowsar Ali, a Somali and Arabic
interpreter,
says just figuring out how to
explain a patient's

30:29.194 --> 30:34.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
symptoms and a doctor's
diagnosis is a puzzle,
words and phrases with no
English equivalent,

30:34.966 --> 30:37.769 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
medical terms like PTSD and
depression that
are unfamiliar.

30:37.803 --> 30:41.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KOWSAR ALI, Jericho Road: It's
actually hard
for them because there's nothing
as depression.

30:41.873 --> 30:45.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say, OK, because that never
existed in
my country.

30:45.043 --> 30:46.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's nothing as depression.

30:46.878 --> 30:50.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Dr. Glick says the
initial relief
refugees feel when they reach
safety often

30:50.916 --> 30:52.451 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
gives way to a new reality.

30:52.484 --> 30:54.352 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

30:54.386 --> 30:58.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MYRON GLICK: All the horrible
things that
happen to people along their
journey to America,

30:58.924 --> 31:01.426 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and yet really they come with
hope.

31:01.460 --> 31:05.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a year, two years in, you
see that hope
dissipate.

31:05.497 --> 31:12.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's really challenging here in
America to
deal with the stresses that are
thrust upon

31:12.637 --> 31:15.907 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
them without the support of
their home community.

31:15.941 --> 31:19.544 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: That sense of
isolation is easing
for some.

31:19.578 --> 31:25.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ali Kadhum arrived in Buffalo in
2008, just
as the fledgling Iraqi community
was taking

31:25.350 --> 31:26.485 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
root.

31:26.518 --> 31:28.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back then, Kadhum says there
were just 25
families.

31:28.186 --> 31:32.524 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ALI KADHUM, Lake Shore
Behavioral Health:
Now it's almost 750 Iraqi
families.

31:32.557 --> 31:37.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Today, he says
Iraqis bump into
each other around town.

31:37.462 --> 31:39.464 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ALI KADHUM: They feel they are
not alone.

31:39.498 --> 31:45.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They feel they are still living
in Iraq, because
people, there's restaurants,
cook their food

31:45.437 --> 31:47.038 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
here.

31:47.072 --> 31:49.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is some people speak their
language,
at least, and they can
communicate.

31:49.941 --> 31:54.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: So many refugees
have moved
here that the population of Erie
County, home

31:54.479 --> 31:58.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Buffalo, is growing for the
first time
since the 1960s.

31:58.517 --> 32:03.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they are reshaping a city
that has struggled
to find its way in the modern
economy.

32:03.989 --> 32:07.292 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Old factories now house
English-language classes.

32:07.325 --> 32:13.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At a small business incubator,
women sell
Iraqi macrame and Rwandan
scarves, and vendors

32:13.331 --> 32:18.303 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
claim to sell the best dim sum
in Buffalo.

32:18.336 --> 32:22.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Refugee children pursue music in
a program
called Buffalo String Works, and
are mentored

32:22.874 --> 32:25.644 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by professional musicians.

32:25.677 --> 32:27.846 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Health systems here are
adapting, too.

32:27.879 --> 32:32.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A Catholic Church once, filled
with Italian
and Irish congregates, recently
reopened as

32:32.751 --> 32:37.189 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a health clinic for new
immigrants.

32:37.222 --> 32:42.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And with so many arrivals from
active war
zones, the University at Buffalo
tapped Dr.

32:42.294 --> 32:46.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kim Griswold to help lead the
Western New
York Center for Survivors of
Torture.

32:46.131 --> 32:47.899 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

32:47.933 --> 32:49.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KIM GRISWOLD, Western New York
Center for
Survivors of Torture: Some of
the folks that

32:49.835 --> 32:55.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we have seen have been horribly
tortured physically,
with scars to prove it,
amputations, other

32:55.040 --> 32:59.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things that we have seen that
are horrific,
cigarette burns, whipping.

32:59.644 --> 33:04.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Kareem Khaleefah,
who worked
for the U.S. Army in Baghdad,
was kidnapped

33:04.182 --> 33:07.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by a Shia militia, lined up with
20 other
men and shot.

33:07.619 --> 33:15.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREEM KHALEEFAH, Worked for
U.S. Army (through
translator): I was like super
lucky that the

33:15.260 --> 33:17.562 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
bullets come on the side of my
body.

33:17.596 --> 33:22.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: He fell to the
ground and pretended
to be dead until nightfall.

33:22.100 --> 33:26.638 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Even in Buffalo's quiet
neighborhoods, those
memories never fade, says
Kadhum, a mental

33:26.671 --> 33:29.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
health counselor at Lake Shore
Behavioral
Health.

33:29.574 --> 33:35.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says many older Iraqis, like
Saja Alnaqeeb
and her husband, Mahmoud, once
lived prosperous,

33:35.213 --> 33:36.348 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
vibrant lives.

33:36.381 --> 33:41.019 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, in 2005, Saja was tortured
and the family
fled.

33:41.052 --> 33:43.889 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now she stays inside, tormented
by her memories.

33:43.922 --> 33:54.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): My
family, sometimes,
they wake up, they find me
screaming at night

33:54.566 --> 33:56.301 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with these nightmares.

33:56.334 --> 33:59.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The images she
sees on the news
are a constant reminder of the
continuing

33:59.804 --> 34:01.473 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
violence in Iraq.

34:01.506 --> 34:05.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She worries about her children
and grandchildren
still in Baghdad.

34:05.277 --> 34:11.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): My
mind is about
them.

34:11.483 --> 34:16.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every time they mention to me
they are unsafe,
they are getting threatened,
they move their

34:16.621 --> 34:23.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
place from place to place just
to make sure
that they are -- protect their
kids and family.

34:23.395 --> 34:29.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The recent spate
of violent
attacks worldwide have fueled
anti-immigrant

34:29.267 --> 34:31.403 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and anti-refugee sentiment.

34:31.436 --> 34:36.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But experts on human migration
say these events
are rare, and, in fact, it's
refugees who

34:36.942 --> 34:39.644 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
often face discrimination and
violence.

34:39.678 --> 34:41.980 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Neil Boothby is a professor at
Columbia University.

34:42.013 --> 34:44.249 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
NEIL BOOTHBY, Columbia
University: There's
going to be language issues.

34:44.282 --> 34:45.917 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's going to be cultural
issues.

34:45.951 --> 34:49.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What happens if a girl wants to
wear a scarf
over her head?

34:49.521 --> 34:51.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How is the community going to
respond to that?

34:51.222 --> 34:54.092 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What if people need to spend a
lot of time
in the mosques?

34:54.125 --> 34:55.660 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How are we going to respond to
that?

34:55.694 --> 34:57.996 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So it's going to be an
adjustment, I think,
for each side.

34:58.029 --> 35:03.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: In Buffalo, the
focus now is
to enroll more people in mental
health counseling.

35:03.935 --> 35:09.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At a Lake Shore clinic,
patients, like Kurd
Bllnd struggle to reconcile
religion, sectarian

35:09.240 --> 35:11.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and ethnic violence that has
persisted for
decades.

35:12.010 --> 35:14.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KURD BLLND, Patient (through
translator):
What happened to the Kurdish in
Iraq, of course

35:14.813 --> 35:17.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you're going to be upset and
angry and anxious.

35:17.515 --> 35:22.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Bllnd, who grew up
in a Kurdish
village in Iraq, was jailed and
interrogated

35:22.220 --> 35:23.855 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for three years in the 1980s.

35:23.888 --> 35:28.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KURD BLLND (through translator):
Since the
age of 12 years until now -- I'm
67 years

35:28.360 --> 35:31.229 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of age -- I didn't see anything
good in life.

35:31.262 --> 35:35.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Two years after he
arrived in
Buffalo, Bllnd reluctantly
agreed to seek

35:35.333 --> 35:36.668 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
help.

35:36.701 --> 35:42.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KURD BLLND: They told me, if you
go there,
somebody talk to you.

35:42.440 --> 35:46.945 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Maybe you forget past, what
happened to you.

35:46.978 --> 35:49.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JESSICA MARMION, Lake Shore
Behavioral Health:
The key stressor, I think, is
isolation.

35:49.247 --> 35:54.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, they come here, they don't
speak the language,
they really only know their
immediate family.

35:54.252 --> 35:58.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Jessica Marmion is
a clinical
social worker who teams up with
interpreter

35:58.256 --> 35:59.958 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Afaf Pickering.

35:59.991 --> 36:01.960 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AFAF PICKERING, Lake Shore
Behavioral Health:
We have like all kinds of people
coming.

36:01.993 --> 36:03.028 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We have lawyers.

36:03.061 --> 36:04.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have businesspeople.

36:04.863 --> 36:09.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have -- you need sometimes to
talk about
your problems, especially coming
from a country

36:09.834 --> 36:11.403 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of war.

36:11.436 --> 36:12.404 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You went through trauma.

36:12.437 --> 36:13.838 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You went through death.

36:13.872 --> 36:15.607 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You went through some violence.

36:15.640 --> 36:17.375 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we're not superhuman.

36:17.409 --> 36:21.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: As new refugees
arrive each
day in Buffalo, known as the
City of Good

36:21.980 --> 36:26.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Neighbors, health care leaders
say they will
continue to listen, to reach
out, and help

36:26.217 --> 36:30.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
refugee families find new
opportunities in
a changing American city.

36:30.422 --> 36:39.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour" and
Kaiser Health News,
I'm Sarah Varney in Buffalo.

36:39.597 --> 36:53.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Last September, a
federal court
in Alabama ruled that the
Birmingham Police

36:53.244 --> 36:59.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Department's disciplinary
practices, including
the use of pepper spray for
minor discipline

36:59.150 --> 37:03.688 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
problems, is in violation of
student rights
and unconstitutional.

37:03.721 --> 37:09.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Attorney Ebony Howard of the
Southern Poverty
Law Center filed the
class-action suit, and

37:09.294 --> 37:13.164 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
returns to court next month when
the police
department's appeal is heard.

37:13.198 --> 37:19.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As part of our year-long Race
Matters conversations
focusing on solutions, special
correspondent

37:19.237 --> 37:25.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Charlayne Hunter-Gault reports
from Birmingham
about reducing tensions between
African-American

37:25.043 --> 37:28.012 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
high school students and the
police.

37:28.046 --> 37:34.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: This
video of a white
South Carolina policeman roughly
ejecting

37:34.285 --> 37:39.724 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a black student from her
classroom went viral
and ignited a conversation about
the proper

37:39.757 --> 37:42.360 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
role for police in schools.

37:42.393 --> 37:47.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ebony Howard, a lawyer with the
Southern Poverty
Law Center, has been involved in
that conversation

37:47.765 --> 37:54.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as a result of her successful
suit against
police macing students in
Montgomery, Alabama.

37:54.139 --> 37:55.507 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ebony Howard, thank you for
joining us.

37:55.540 --> 37:57.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EBONY HOWARD, Southern Poverty
Law Center:
Thank you for having me.

37:57.342 --> 38:01.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Can you
tell us briefly
about the case you won in
Birmingham last

38:01.379 --> 38:02.413 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
year?

38:02.447 --> 38:04.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
EBONY HOWARD: Sure.

