55:32.262 --> 55:34.031 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and psychological trauma.

55:34.064 --> 55:35.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Sarah
Varney brings
us this report about how one
city, Buffalo,

55:35.966 --> 55:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
New York, is adapting. Her story
was produced
in collaboration with our
partner Kaiser Health

55:36.266 --> 55:38.101 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
News.

55:38.135 --> 55:39.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Since Murhaf,
Ghenwa, and their
children moved here from Syria,
even mundane

55:39.469 --> 55:40.103 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tasks like cooking and homework
have become
more complicated.

55:40.137 --> 55:41.972 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: They have 10 airplanes.

55:42.005 --> 55:43.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Unaccustomed tote
this new life,
the family relies on help from
Hassan Alishaqi

55:43.140 --> 55:44.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from a local resettlement agency
called Journey's
End.

55:44.942 --> 55:46.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Refugee agencies help families
like this one
find housing and jobs, get
medical care and

55:46.777 --> 55:48.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
health insurance and enroll in
English classes
and schools. They fled Syria
after civil war

55:48.745 --> 55:50.480 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
erupted there in 2011,
unleashing an exodus
of more than four million
refugees. The destruction

55:50.514 --> 55:50.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and violence came close to
Murhaf's family
during one their last nights in
the city of

55:50.814 --> 55:52.549 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Homs.

55:52.583 --> 55:54.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): Some
bullets came
to my house through the window.
And I was

55:54.418 --> 55:54.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
afraid for the safety of my
kids. They never
sleep because of -- it's just
very hard for

55:54.851 --> 55:56.853 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
them to sleep.

55:56.887 --> 55:58.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: After a year in
Cairo and exhaustive
security checks, the family
arrived in Buffalo,

55:58.722 --> 56:00.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a quiet city on the edge of Lake
Erie. And
like many new arrivals here,
they're struggling

56:00.490 --> 56:00.891 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with the aftermath of their
horrific journey
as they attempt to build
healthier lives in

56:00.924 --> 56:02.793 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their new home.

56:02.826 --> 56:04.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
More than 90 percent of the
refugees who resettle
to New York live in Upstate New
York. The

56:04.728 --> 56:06.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
city of Buffalo has become a
welcoming haven
for many of them. But over the
last 15 years,

56:06.496 --> 56:07.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the countries and conflicts they
come from
have changed. And the health
care needs of

56:07.164 --> 56:08.832 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
refugees are changing, too.

56:08.865 --> 56:10.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jericho Road is a community
health center
in Buffalo that has long treated
refugees

56:10.634 --> 56:12.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from some of the world's poorest
countries,
including Myanmar, Bhutan, Sudan
and Somalia.

56:12.469 --> 56:14.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The clinic is a crossroads of
languages and
customs. New refugees receive
free medical

56:14.371 --> 56:14.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
assistance from the federal
government for
eight months. Then they can buy
private insurance

56:14.938 --> 56:16.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or enroll in Medicaid.

56:16.740 --> 56:17.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. MYRON GLICK, Jericho Road:
When you came,
we found that your T.B. test was
positive.

56:17.975 --> 56:19.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I think you are now taking
medicine for
that, right?

56:19.843 --> 56:21.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The clinic's
founder, Dr. Myron
Glick, often treats refugees for
tuberculosis,

56:21.678 --> 56:23.513 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
